EST. 2010 Galveston Island is a seafood loverâ€™s paradise all year round, but this September, Yagaâ€™s Entertainment will bring foodies a little taste of heaven at the Galveston Island Shrimp Festival. Featuring some of the best shrimp gumbo the Gulf Coast has to offer, the cook-off will be held in the Historic Strand District beginning at 10 a.m. on Saturday, September 27, 2025. This event will also feature the Shrimp Scamper 5k Fun Run, Ron Hoover Boat Show , vendor exhibits, and live music! Click here to view the full festival schedule. Visitors to the festival will be able to purchase a Gumbo Stroll ticket in advance for a limited time only. This ticket will sell out! This ticket will allow guests to sample gumbo from cook-off teams comprised of amateurs and professionals. Professional teams from some of Galveston Islandâ€™s famous restaurants will also be selling various dishes for public purchase. A portion of event proceeds will benefit the Resource and Crisis Center, Justin Hughes Fund, and University of Texas Medical Branch. Get Discount Tickets! Thank You To Our 2025 Sponsors! Donâ€™t miss the 20th Annual Little River ShrimpFest on Saturday, October 11th and Sunday, October 12th, 2025 from 10 a.m. â€“ 5 p.m. at the Historic Little River Waterfront. Festival goers can expect to enjoy 2 stages of live music, stilt walkers, balloon artists, and more than 100 different vendors- including a variety of art and craft vendors, business expos, and community organizations. Shrimp and fresh local seafood will be served by the local waterfront restaurants and your festival food favorites will be available from a variety of talented food vendors. Fun for the whole family!
